programme.title: E13: Grunt Call Turns Giant Buck, Rattling In A Illinois Brute
programme.desc: Picking up right where we left off, the November 6th train continues rolling with multiple team members looking to take advantage of the best time of year to be a bow hunter. Brothers Avery and Aidan Epperson hang and hunt overlooking an untouched green plot on their home property and tag a Missouri stud. Justin Karns similarly hunts his own home farm and enjoys a beautiful encounter with a giant buck that calls the piece home. Justin Kamps and good friend Jonny Kammenga seal the deal on another epic rut hunt, rattling in an Illinois bruiser they call "Big Mac."

programme.title: Owen Almost Punches Two Buck Tags, Scrape Line Stud

Setup over a hot scrape line surrounded by acorns, Korey Wolfe has the perfect bow hunt in central Missouri that ends with a stud buck on the ground. Zach Rozmus fine tunes what he expects to be his best stand in the next few weeks. Mike Reed wastes no time following the epic hunt for Vinny and is back in the woods making final preparations for his upcoming vacation. Owen Reigler takes another shot at the Enforcer buck recruiting the buck decoy to draw the aggressive deer into range. By the end of the evening, Owen nearly punches two tags on two great bucks resulting in one of the most action filled October evenings in the deer woods we can remember.
